Commercial Vehicle Group - Wikipedia





















 






Commercial Vehicle Group

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Commercial Vehicle Group


Type

Public


Traded as
NASDAQ: CVGI


Industry
Truck manufacturing


Headquarters
New Albany, Ohio, United States



Key people

Pat Miller, President & CEO
C. Timothy Trenary, CFO


Website
http://www.cvgrp.com/


Commercial Vehicle Group (CVG) is a global supplier of complete cab systems in the heavy-duty truck, construction and agricultural equipment markets including the specialty and military transportation markets. The company went public in 2004, the same year they opened their Shanghai facility.[1] CVG maintains operations in North America, Europe, Asia, and Australia. CVG employs over 7,000 employees worldwide, and revenues in fiscal year 2013 were $747.7M.[2]
References[edit]



^ http://library.corporate-ir.net/library/18/180/180209/items/280213/BBT021408.pdf
^ http://ir.cvgrp.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=180209&p=irol-reportsannual







 
